1
00:00:01,660 --> 00:00:08,770
Now we have the form to create a category, but with .net core, we have tag helpers that we can use

2
00:00:08,770 --> 00:00:15,910
to make this input fields more dynamic because basically we have to bind somewhere that this input field

3
00:00:15,910 --> 00:00:17,410
is for category name.

4
00:00:17,410 --> 00:00:20,380
And the next one here is for display order.

5
00:00:20,800 --> 00:00:25,450
In older versions of .net, we used to bind them with name property.

6
00:00:25,480 --> 00:00:29,320
When we post the form we used to retrieve and assign them.

7
00:00:29,320 --> 00:00:32,800
But .net core has made everything super simple.

8
00:00:33,250 --> 00:00:41,860
We have the model that we have defined here, so with input we have tag helpers which is ASP hyphen

9
00:00:41,860 --> 00:00:42,790
for.

10
00:00:43,890 --> 00:00:44,730
Inside there.

11
00:00:44,730 --> 00:00:50,820
We have to define what this input field will be responsible for and that is for name.

12
00:00:51,300 --> 00:00:58,260
Now, if you think how name is working here, that is because we have category model and that has a

13
00:00:58,260 --> 00:01:00,990
property with the value of name.

14
00:01:01,380 --> 00:01:04,620
If you write name one here, it will not work.

15
00:01:04,709 --> 00:01:11,820
You can see category does not contain a definition for name, so it will only have those properties

16
00:01:11,820 --> 00:01:14,130
which are defined in your model.

17
00:01:14,580 --> 00:01:20,350
And the best part is if you have ASP four, then you do not have to define type as well.

18
00:01:20,370 --> 00:01:24,990
It will automatically find out the type based on the property name.

19
00:01:25,900 --> 00:01:32,050
So the next one here, we will say ASP for that will be for display order.

20
00:01:32,080 --> 00:01:36,160
We type that and IntelliSense already displays that.

21
00:01:37,210 --> 00:01:40,240
Same thing we have for the label name as well.

22
00:01:40,660 --> 00:01:49,300
So if we use ASP for we do not have to define display order here, it will automatically add that and

23
00:01:49,300 --> 00:01:50,500
let me show that.

24
00:01:51,880 --> 00:01:54,550
We will remove the category name here.

25
00:01:54,610 --> 00:01:58,090
Save them and let's go back.

26
00:01:58,630 --> 00:01:59,250
Great.

27
00:01:59,260 --> 00:02:02,380
You can see name and display order.

28
00:02:02,950 --> 00:02:05,230
But then we have another issue.

29
00:02:05,440 --> 00:02:08,740
The property names that we have does not have a space.

30
00:02:08,860 --> 00:02:12,340
What if we want to add a space in display order?

31
00:02:13,580 --> 00:02:14,210
For that.

32
00:02:14,210 --> 00:02:18,690
We have data annotations that we have to add on our model.

33
00:02:18,710 --> 00:02:20,060
Where is that?

34
00:02:20,090 --> 00:02:22,220
We have the category model.

35
00:02:22,880 --> 00:02:25,520
Let me stop the application here.

36
00:02:26,590 --> 00:02:33,010
We have seen the data annotations that were required for entity framework core, but we can also add

37
00:02:33,010 --> 00:02:39,640
data annotations that are useful for client side UI or client side validation.

38
00:02:40,370 --> 00:02:43,190
We have something called as display name.

39
00:02:43,460 --> 00:02:46,790
And there we have to write the name that we want.

40
00:02:46,970 --> 00:02:51,800
So when it is being displayed, we want display order with a space.

41
00:02:51,800 --> 00:02:56,660
And where we have the name, let's say we want to display name.

42
00:02:58,860 --> 00:03:00,450
Of category name.

43
00:03:01,500 --> 00:03:05,250
With that configured, let me run the application again.

44
00:03:06,260 --> 00:03:10,760
So let me go to category again and create new category.

45
00:03:11,060 --> 00:03:11,660
Perfect.

46
00:03:11,690 --> 00:03:14,960
Now we have the category name and display order.

47
00:03:15,110 --> 00:03:17,750
The textbox here looks off.

48
00:03:17,750 --> 00:03:19,730
Let me go back here.

49
00:03:19,910 --> 00:03:20,780
Whoops.

50
00:03:21,810 --> 00:03:29,470
Sometimes you will have to stop and restart for the UI changes as well, but that should be okay.

51
00:03:29,490 --> 00:03:34,120
Let's go back here and perfect now.

52
00:03:34,140 --> 00:03:40,620
Best thing when we are using ASP four and the property name are the same for label and input.

53
00:03:40,650 --> 00:03:46,080
If you click on the label, it will automatically highlight the input field.

54
00:03:46,650 --> 00:03:50,760
So that is also done with the help of Tag Helper.

55
00:03:51,360 --> 00:03:53,100
You can see display order.

56
00:03:53,100 --> 00:03:59,370
It automatically knows it's an integer value and it defines that right here.

57
00:03:59,670 --> 00:04:03,660
So that is the beauty of working with tag helpers.

58
00:04:04,630 --> 00:04:08,980
With that configured, let me continue from the next video.

